            "en-x-generated": "<h3>Nuisance premium</h3><h4>Notification letter</h4><p>If you qualify for the nuisance premium, the Agency for Innovation &amp; Enterprise (Agentschap Innoveren &amp; Ondernemen - Vlaio) will notify your company <strong>before the start date of the work</strong>. This is done digitally, in your e-box, or by post, if you have not yet activated your e-box. <a href=\"https://www.vlaio.be/nl/subsidies-financiering/hinderpremie/aanvraagprocedure-hinderpremie/vlaio-gebruikt-digitale-overheidspost\">More information on using the eBox for enterprises</a> can be found on the VLAIO website. In this notification letter, you will receive more information about the upcoming works and about the possibility of applying for a nuisance premium and/or additional closure premium.</p><h4>Application</h4><p>You submit your premium application <a href=\"https://www.hinderpremie.be/\">via the web application</a>. You do this</p><ul><li>at the latest <strong>60 days after the date</strong> mentioned in the salutation of the letter</li><li><strong>in any case before the scheduled end date of the work</strong> (even if it is less than 60 days).</li></ul><p>If your application deadline has passed (i.e. if you are late with your application), you will get the message that your <strong>'file has been cancelled'</strong>. In those cases, nothing more can be done to still apply for the payout. So the message is: too late is irrevocably too late.</p><h4>Payout</h4><p>Shortly after the application and after the data have been checked by the agency, the nuisance premium is paid <strong>out automatically</strong>.</p><h3>Additional closure premium</h3><p>If you do have to close your doors during the works, if you meet the conditions you can also apply for the additional closure premium <a href=\"https://www.hinderpremie.be/\">via the same web application as the nuisance premium</a>. You do so:</p><ul><li><strong>at the earliest on the day the public works begin</strong></li><li><strong>at the latest on the day your closure period starts.</strong></li></ul><h4>Request per period of 30 calendar days</h4><p>You must submit a <strong>new application</strong> for a nuisance allowance per 30-day period. The <strong>first</strong> time you apply for the additional closure period, the specified closure period may <strong>not exceed 51 days</strong>. You then apply for the premiums for all subsequent closure periods in <strong>blocks of up to 30 calendar days</strong>.</p><h3>Individual closure premium</h3><p>Companies eligible for the individual closure premium also submit their application <a href=\"https://www.hinderpremie.be/\">via the web application</a>. The first time you apply for the separate closure period, the specified closure period may <strong>not exceed 37 days</strong>. You apply for the premiums for subsequent closure periods in <strong>blocks of up to 30 calendar days</strong>. You must <a href=\"https://www.vlaio.be/nl/subsidies-financiering/hinderpremie/aanvraagprocedure/je-ondervindt-ernstige-hinder-door-werken/je#Bewijslast\">provide</a> evidence in your application that the closure of the establishment is due to public works.</p><h3>Control</h3><p>The Innovation &amp; Enterprise Agency (VLAIO) may carry out checks at any time. If these show that a premium was paid unduly or that an excessive amount was paid, the agency may reclaim all or part of the premium.</p>",
