            "en-x-generated": "<h3>Nuisance premium</h3><p>The nuisance premium amounts to <strong>EUR 2</strong>,000. </p><p>Per work assignment, there is always <strong>only one entitlement to a nuisance premium</strong>, regardless of how long the works last. Moreover, a nuisance premium can only be received once every 365 days. If new works take place, an entitlement to a nuisance premium can arise again, provided that both the company and the public works again fulfil all conditions at that time. But those works will then only entitle you to a nuisance premium 365 days after the previous nuisance premium was paid.</p><p>Your company can apply for the premium <strong>a maximum of once a year and once per nuisance period</strong> (the period during which the works causing serious nuisance take place). For public works that altogether last more than 1 year, you can therefore get the nuisance premium only once.</p><h3>Closure premium</h3><p>The closure premium amounts to <strong>80 euros per day</strong> that your establishment actually remains closed. </p><p><strong>The premium starts running from the 22nd calendar day</strong> of the specified closure period. If the affected establishment is normally open less than 5 days a week, the additional closure premium will be granted only for the days on which the establishment would be open under normal circumstances. In this case, the closure premium is therefore not granted for all days of the specified closure period.</p><p>The nuisance premium and closure premium are <a href=\"https://www.vlaio.be/nl/begeleiding-advies/financiering/overheidsmaatregelen/veelgestelde-vragen-welke-subsidies-worden-vrijgesteld-van-belasting-vrijgesteld-van-belasting-vrijgesteld-van-belasting-vrijgesteld-van-belasting\">exempt </a>from both personal and corporate income tax. </p>",
