            "en": "<p><strong>The premium applies to buildings </strong></p><ul><li>that are not houses or flats </li><li>that are connected to the electricity grid before 1 January 2014, or </li><li>for which the integrated environment permit for town planning activities was granted over five years ago, and that meet the EPB requirements and for which the EPB declaration was submitted on time. </li></ul><p><strong>Requirements for solar panels </strong></p><ul><li>New solar panels with an inverter power less than or equal to 10 kVA. </li><li><a href=\"https://rescert.be/nl/list?res_category=2\">Installed or validated by a contractor with a certificate of competence.</a></li><li>If it is a heated building, the roof on which the solar panels are installed must also be insulated (Rd value of at least 3 m<sup>2</sup>K/W). </li><li>The premium amount is determined by the inspection date (i.e. no later than 31 December 2022 to be eligible for the 2022 premium). </li></ul><p>You can find all the requirements and details on the Dutch-language webpage <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/en/fluvius-premium-for-solar-panels-for-non-residential-buildings\">‘Premie van Fluvius voor zonnepanelen voor niet- woongebouwen’ </a>(Fluvius premium for solar panels for non-residential buildings). </p><p><strong>Investors in solar panels can apply for the premium</strong>. </p>"
